==English==
===Interjection phrase===
'''[[too]] [[bad]]'''

#{{idiom}} That's a pity, that's unfortunate.
#:''It's '''too bad''' you can't attend tonight.''

====Usage note====
*'''Too bad''' is used to express sympathy at another's misfortune, or, with an ironic tone, to express pleasure with or disinterest in another's misfortune.

====Synonyms====
*[[pity]], [[shame]], [[that's a pity]], [[that's a shame]], [[that's too bad]], [[what a pity]], [[what a shame]]